@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'ArcheoBot' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench
must have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  All the areas to search are surrounded by a thick red brick wall,
which is undestructible, except for two wall sections that are
located on either side of the exit. The area inside is filled with
various artifacts, each occupying 2 spaces horizontally. Your
spaceship is located on the top wall, near the exit of the area.

  Playing 'ArcheoBot' is pretty simple: click in the general area
(or by using the cursor keys), where you want to move your
ArcheoBot, which always appear in the center of a 5 by 5 spaces
display. To help you, a small display at right shows where your
ArcheoBot is located in the game area.

  You can move toward empty spaces or any artifact (trashcan,
automobile, pickup truck, human skeleton) that is located next to
the ArcheoBot's position. If rocks are blocking the way, you can
blast them up by using one of the explosive charges that are carried
by the 'Bot. The blast will always be in the direction the ArcheoBot
is moving. Note that no blast will happen if the ArcheoBot is
located next to the brick wall surrounding the research area, except
for the 2 'removeable' brick walls sections -indicated by the
absence of white 'mortar' lines in them- which are located at each
side of the entrance...

  ...Also, watch out that a blast does not blow up any part of
artifacts nearby... unless you have no choice. If you do blow up
part of artifacts, that will penalize you a bit as you will lose
those precious artifacts.

  When you collect artifacts, the number under 'Artifacts' at the
right of the game display will increase according to the value of
the collected artifacts, as the following table indicates:

Garbage:                 1 artifact point per half unit
Automobile/pickup truck: 3 artifact points per half unit
Skeleton:                5 artifact points per half unit

  When you have collected some artifacts, you can return to the
spaceship to convert those artifacts into points. To do so, the
ArcheoBot has to 'touch' the spaceship. The number of points you
get is calculated according to the total value of the artifacts,
multiplied by the number of remaining explosive charges. So the
more charges your 'Bot has, the more points you will get...

  As the ArcheoBot blows up rocks, some other rocks might cave-in,
this could block an already cleared-up path in the process. Also,
be aware that your ArcheoBot can carry a maximum of 10 explosive
charges at all times. As long as there is at least one charge, the
ArcheoBot can freely move in the area... But, when it runs out of
charges, the ArcheoBot still has a small quantity of backup energy
-enough for 40 moves- so it can still return to the spaceship to
get an additional supply of 10 charges. If that energy runs out,
the ArcheoBot will 'shutdown'. When that happens, you lose an
ArcheoBot and a cross will appear at the ArcheoBot's former
location, then you will have to send another of your ArcheoBots to
retrieve the artifacts the other ArcheoBot had accumulated.

  When an area is cleared of artifacts, the game displays a new area
and the game continues, until you clear the last area ...or you lose
your third and last ArcheoBot.

  To quit the game, click on the game window's closebutton or press
the 'Esc' key.

  Have fun!

